tack and Accidents.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> There is no public survey conducted </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in Afghanistan for the exact number of P.W.D, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">but random survey indicated that there are more than 3 million</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> people living with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">different type</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of disability including the above War victims figures.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In Afghanistan, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Persons with disability especially women /children </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are not aware of their social, political and economic rights</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> because, there are still no comprehensive services available for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">P.W.D</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> neither from government and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nor from the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">International community such as UN and others stakeholders.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-