only ICRC has some facilities but they </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are only operating</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> mainly in Kabul, Mazar, Jalalabbad, Hirat. Theses provinces cannot say yes to the solution of the whole Afghanistan</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> people with disability</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. ICRC has no limitation from others provinces</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> they say yes to any Afghan with disability,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> but for persons with disability </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">it </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is difficult </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for coming from one province</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> or far district to another long distance due to their poverty it is difficult to afford the expensive rent of bus with huge challengeable physical accessibility before receive artificial limbs or outhouses.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#f79646; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Employability of persons with disability in Afghanistan:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Employment is an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">parts of the life for every one</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> also it is basic rights</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of the human being,</span><span style="font-f